<DOC><DOCNO> AP880630-0263 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-30-88 2343EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a AM-BRF--BabyHearts     06-30 0133</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Baby Hearts,0134</SECOND><HEAD>World's Youngest Transplant Recipient Will Go Home To Canada OnFriday</HEAD><DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Paul Holc will go home to Canada on Friday,eight months after he became the world's youngest transplantpatient.   The 8-month-old heart patient has progressed so well since hissurgery Oct. 16 that ``he is going home sooner than the one year weusually keep the babies,'' said Anita Rockwell, spokeswoman forLoma Linda University Medical Center.   Since his transplant, Paul and his parents, Gordon and AliceHolc, have stayed in a temporary residence near Loma Linda, 60miles east of Los Angeles. They live in the Vancouver suburb ofSurrey.   Once home, he will continue to receive medicines to preventrejection of the heart he received three hours after birth, Ms.Rockwell said.</TEXT></DOC>